Here's how to set up an API for Hebrew transcription on runpod.io:

1. **Sign up for runpod.io**:
   - Go to [runpod.io](https://www.runpod.io/?ref=06octndf) and sign up. Using our referral link would be greatly appreciated.

2. **Set up the endpoint**:
   - Visit the following link: [github.com/ivrit-ai/runpod-serverless](https://github.com/ivrit-ai/runpod-serverless/blob/main/README.md)
   - Follow the instructions in the README file to set up the endpoint.

3. **Connect to the endpoint**:
   - Once you've set up the endpoint, you will have a live Hebrew transcription API.

### Costs
- The cost is $0.58 per machine hour, which is approximately $0.1 (10 cents) per hour of transcribed content in Hebrew.
- This is more than 10 times cheaper than most professional services.

